<item>
            <title>[SEC-2501] Provide a simpler way to customize X-Frame-Options mode used by default in the Java config</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2501</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Customizing the X-Frame-Options mode used by default in the Java config is not an unlikely customization. For example the SockJS protocol has two iframe based protocols, which are actually the main choice when running in IE 8, 9. Both transports fail with Spring Security&apos;s Java config out of the box. &lt;/p&gt;

